      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Parts of the Network Monitoring System</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The
network monitoring system consists of:</p>
         <ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The communication interface, extends the signal from the controller
board and to the smart slot translator.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The smart slot translator, converts the signal from the controller
board to another type of protocol. Allows for local connection to
the NMC.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Network Management Card (NMC)</b>, offers secure local
and/or remote monitoring of Reality systems.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The options slot, is an additional slot for an optional extra
card. It can be used to for example connect another NMC card for additional
ports, to use different settings or for redundancy.</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </section>
